name: ES File Explorer userReturn File
summary: Learn about .USERRETURN files and view a list of programs that open them.

windows.name: Open over 400 file formats with File Viewer Plus.Free Download

content: ES File Explorer is a third-party Android app that allows users to explore and manage their files. In 2019, Google removed ES File Explorer from the Google Play Store, claiming that the app (and other Baidu apps) were committing click fraud.

One of the files ES File Explorer creates and places on a user's device is a USERRETURN file. This file contains two unique, user-specific numbers. However, what these numbers are used for is unknown.

description: A USERRETURN file is a text file created by ES File Explorer, a file manager for Android. It contains a small amount of text, including two numbers. Its purpose is unknown.

instructions: USERRETURN files are referenced by ES File Explorer (Android) and not meant to be opened and edited. However, you can use any text editor to open a USERRETURN file and view the text it contains.
